title: Farm House at Le Croisic
medium: Graphite on thick cream wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
description: Horizontal sheet that has been cut down from a larger one depicting a large masonry farm house with thatched or tiled roof.  It consists of a central building with a projecting tower and turret flanked by two large dormers, and two smaller, single-story wings projecting on either side.  There are chimney stacks at either end of the roof line.
